s libraries and archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-05-06T15:08:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.lexm.uni-hamburg.de/content/index.xml\">LexM</a> - Encyclopedia of musicians persecuted during the Nazi era.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-04-13T12:57:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.archivportal-d.de/\">Archivportal</a> - German archives search engine.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.bavarikon.de/\">Bavarikon</a> - Collection of Bavarian maps, places, newspapers etc.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.deutsche-digitale-bibliothek.de/\">Deutsche Digitale Bibliothek</a> - Over 12 million objects.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.digitale-sammlungen.de/\">Digitale Sammlungen</a> - Collections of the Munich Digitization Center.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.leo-bw.de/\">leo bw</a> - Platform of the State Archives of Baden-Württemberg.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://digital.slub-dresden.de/kollektionen/\">SLUB Dresden</a> - Over 1.8 million graphic media (photographs, maps, drawings).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ub.uni-heidelberg.de/helios/digi/digilit.html\">UB Heidelberg</a> - Manuscripts, documents, maps and literature.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://digital.zlb.de/\">ZLB</a> - Collections of the Berlin Central and State Library.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>More Awesome</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tempopedia.org/\">Tempopedia</a> - Digital History Directory.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-31T09:31:15.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Austria</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://anno.onb.ac.at/\">ANNO</a> - Austrian Newspapers online.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mapire.eu/\">Mapire</a> - Interactive historical maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.monasterium.net/mom/home\">Monasterium</a> - Deeds from all over Europe.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://sammlungen.ub.uni-frankfurt.de/\">Uni Frankfurt</a> - Rare prints, manuscripts, bequests and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.bl.uk/catalogues-and-collections/digital-collections\">British Library</a> - Maps, manuscripts and sounds.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/\">Chronicling America</a> - America's historic newspapers from 1777-1963.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.davidrumsey.com/\">David Rumsey Map Collection</a> - Over 94,000 maps and related images.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dp.la/\">Digital Public Library of America</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eugenicsarchive.ca/\">Eugenics Archive</a> - Scholars, survivors, students, and community partners in challenging eugenics.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.archeco.info/\">arCHeco</a> - Index of economic collections in archives of Switzerland and Liechtenstein.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.kartenportal.ch/\">Kartenportal</a> - Search engine for maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-02-03T18:53:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>France</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ina.fr/\">Institut national de l'audiovisuel</a> - INA is a repository of French radio and television audiovisual archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-01-06T07:42:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://bitsavers.trailing-edge.com/\">Bitsavers.org</a> - Computer code, reference manuals, and magazines.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-01-06T07:42:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.wdl.org/\">World Digital Library</a> - WDL is an international digital library operated by UNESCO and the United States Library of Congress.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-01-06T07:42:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>More Awesome</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/maehr/awesome-digital-history/wiki\">Digital History Wiki</a> - Everything that did not make it into the Awesome Digital History list.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-01-06T07:42:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gutenberg.org/\">Project Gutenberg</a> - A library of over 60,000 free eBooks.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.digitales-deutsches-frauenarchiv.de/\">Digitales Deutsches Frauenarchiv</a> - An interactive portal on the history of women's movements in Germany.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://docupedia.de/\">Docupedia</a> - Terms, methods, and debates in contemporary history research.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://fxtop.com/\">fxtop.com</a> - Forex rate history since 1953.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://archive.org/\">Internet Archive</a> - Non-profit library of millions of free books, movies, software, music, websites, and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.marxists.org/\">Marxist Internet Archive</a> - Everything you ever wanted to know about Marx (and other important socialists).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://archive.org/web/\">WayBackMachine</a> - Explore more than 486 billion web pages saved over time.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Great Britain</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.oldbaileyonline.org/\">The Proceedings of the Old Bailey</a> - London's Central Criminal Court, 1674 to 1913.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Great Britain</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://data.nls.uk/data/\">NLS</a> - Data collections from the National Library of Scotland.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Netherlands</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.delpher.nl/\">Delpher</a> - More than 100 million pages from Dutch newspapers, books and magazines.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://legacy.lib.utexas.edu/maps/\">Perry-Castañeda Library Map Collection</a> - More than 250,000 maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://library.harvard.edu/collections/women-working-1800-1930\">Women Working 1800-1930</a> - An exploration of women's impact on the economic life of the United States between 1800 and the Great Depression.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.archives-online.org/\">Archives Online</a> - Archival search engine for Switzerland.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.digithek.ch/de/\">Digithek</a> - A collection of digital finding aids for secondary and vocational schools.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.e-newspaperarchives.ch/\">e-newspaperarchives.ch</a> - Swiss newspapers.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.e-periodica.ch/\">E-Periodica</a> - Swiss journals.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.e-rara.ch/\">e-rara</a> - The platform for digitised rare books from Swiss libraries.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hls-dhs-dss.ch/\">Historical Encyclopedia of Switzerland</a> - Encyclopedia on Swiss history.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://impresso-project.ch/\">impresso</a> - Historical newspaper collections of the Swiss National Library, the National Library of Luxembourg, the Neue Zürcher Zeitung, Le Temps, the Valais State Archives and the Swiss Economic Archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.infoclio.ch/en/edition-projects\">infoclio.ch Edition projects</a> - A database containing current historical edition projects in Switzerland.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.letempsarchives.ch/\">Le Temps</a> - Archive of Gazette de Lausanne et du Journal de Genève.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://map.geo.admin.ch/\">map.geo.admin.ch</a> - Journey through time via maps of Switzerland.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.memobase.ch/\">MEMOBASE</a> - Provides access to 415'634 audiovisual documents from 67 Swiss memory institutions.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://programminghistorian.org/\">The Programming Historian</a> - Novice-friendly, peer-reviewed tutorials that help humanists learn a wide range of digital tools, techniques, and workflows to facilitate research and teaching.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wethink.hypotheses.org/\">We think History</a> - News about and innovations from digital history.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>More Awesome</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/watson/awesome-computer-history\">Computer History</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/watson/awesome-computer-history\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2088,\"repo\":\"watson/awesome-computer-history\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An Awesome List of computer history videos, documentaries and related folklore.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>More Awesome</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com