ources/awesome-scientific-writing#readme\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">204</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":204,\"repo\":\"writing-resources/awesome-scientific-writing\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-20T15:31:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://locallinkages.org/\">Local Linkages</a> - How to frame questions about the past, identify sources to answer those questions, place them in context, and present that historical interpretation online in a digital form.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-11-16T08:46:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://comp-think.github.io/\">The CTP Book</a> - A book for teaching Computational Thinking and Programming skills to people with a background in the Humanities.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-03T07:31:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.amtsdruckschriften.bar.admin.ch/\">Amtsdruckschriften</a> - Federal Gazette, Administrative Case Law of the Federal Authorities and more documents from the Swiss Federal Archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-06-01T08:43:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://archives.cendari.dariah.eu/\">CENDARI</a> - Search engine for libraries containing resources on the Medieval era and World War One.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.spiegel.de/dienste/besser-surfen-auf-spiegel-online-suchen-im-archiv-a-676489.html\">Spiegel Online</a> - SPIEGEL archive since 1947.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://zefys.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/\">Zefys</a> - Historical German newspapers.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>North America</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://repository.duke.edu/dc/adaccess\">Ad*Access</a> - Over 7,000 U.S. and Canadian advertisements covering five product categories - Beauty and Hygiene, Radio, Television, Transportation, and World War II propaganda - dated between 1911 and 1955.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cosmov.uzh.ch/\">COSMOV</a> - COSMOV includes a digital edition of the events of the Zurich summer of 1968.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://e-codices.ch/\">e-codices</a> - Virtual manuscript library of Switzerland containing 2297 manuscripts from 92 different collections.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.e-manuscripta.ch/\">e-manuscripta</a> - Manuscript material from Swiss libraries and archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.sfa-laboratory.ch/sr/cubestest/index.php\">timeSTAT Cubes</a> - The Federal Council reports to parliament on income and expenditure for the past years.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://workbook.craftingdigitalhistory.ca/\">HIST3814o</a> - Methods and Readings in Digital History by Shawn Graham at  Carleton University.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cblevins.github.io/f19-dig-hist/\">HIST 7370</a> - Methods and Readings in Digital History by Cameron Blevins at Northeastern University.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://guides.lib.uci.edu/history/history_dh\">UCI Digital History</a> - Overview on the field of Digital History and Digital Humanities.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-29T07:52:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.e-gs.ethz.ch/\">e-gs</a> - Online web portal of the ETH Zurich Graphics Collection.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-03-29T16:16:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Germany</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.projekt-gutenberg.org/\">Projekt Gutenberg</a> - Contains 10'000 works by over 2'000 authors in German.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-28T08:31:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Global</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.oldmapsonline.org/\">OldMapsOnline</a> - Maps, starting in the 17th century.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-12-21T11:10:31.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.archivesportaleurope.net/\">Archives Portal Europe</a> - European archives search engine.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Europe</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.europeana.eu/\">Europeana</a> - Search engine for European textual and non-textual archival sources.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>France</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gallica.bnf.fr/\">Gallica</a> - Digital library of the National Library of France.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://histhub.ch/\">histHub</a> - Search engine for all major standadized data APIs.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://industriekultur.ch/\">Industriekultur</a> - Swiss national inventory of industry artifacts.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://chnm.gmu.edu/digitalhistory/\">Digital History Guide</a> - Introduction to the web for historians—teachers and students, archivists and museum curators, professors as well as amateur enthusiasts—who wish to produce online historical work, or to build upon and improve the projects they have already started in this important new medium.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-30T10:36:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.dodis.ch/\">Diplomatic Documents of Switzerland</a> - Diplomatic documents of Switzerland.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-29T10:59:47.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Archives and primary sources</h2><h3>Switzerland</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hsso.ch/\">HSSO</a> - Historical statistics of Switzerland online.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-29T10:59:47.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.adfontes.uzh.ch/\">AdFontes</a> - An Introduction to Working with Sources in the Archive.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-29T10:59:47.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://guides.clio-online.de/\">Clio Guide</a> - A handbook on digital resources for 